article.headline: Lehigh 55, Central Connecticut State 52
article.story: BETHLEHEM, Pa. (AP) -- Freshman Marquis Hall hit a key jumper in the final minute and Jose Olivero finished with 14 points to lead Lehigh to a 55-52 victory over Central Connecticut State on Saturday night. Hall made a jumper with 57 seconds left to give Lehigh the lead for the second time in the second half. Olivero scored in double figures for the 16th straight game for the Mountain Hawks (4-6). Kyle Neptune scored 12 points, Bryan White nine and Jason Mgebroff and Hall each finished with eight. Javier Mojica led Central Connecticut (2-5) with 20 points. Tristan Blackwood made a jumper with 1:34 remaining that gave Central Connecticut a 52-51 lead. After a timeout, Hall hit his jumper to put Lehigh ahead to stay. Lehigh shot just over 39 percent and outrebounded the Blue Devils 36-27. Central Connecticut shot 43 percent.
